# Zero-Gate Health Check (mandatory)

After **any** change under `web/`, `sites/`, `Frontend_Nextjs/`, or `AI-BOS/`, you MUST verify **0 gate failures** before telling the user the task is done. Do not skip gates because a change "looks small."

## Definition: zero gate

**Zero gate = every applicable check exits 0 with no errors, no test failures, and no unresolved diagnostics on touched files** (TypeScript, ESLint, cSpell, build, CI release gates).

If a gate fails, fix the root cause and re-run until all pass. Never hand off with known red diagnostics.

## Post-change verification matrix

### Always (every edit)

1. **IDE diagnostics** — run `ReadLints` on every file you created or modified; fix all errors and warnings (including cSpell on markdown/TSX).
2. **Project dictionary** — brand and tech terms belong in root `cspell.json`; do not silence legitimate typos with inline ignores.

### `web/` (Growrix OS production app)

Run from `web/` in this order; stop and fix on first failure:

```bash
npm run lint
npm run typecheck
npm run perf:budgets
npm run test
npm run build
npm run test:e2e -- tests/e2e/release-gates.spec.ts --project=desktop-chrome
```

Or the bundled script:

```bash
npm run health:check
```

**Release gates (must be 0 failures):** accessibility smoke, security headers, health endpoints, homepage load ≤5s, resource budget ≤30, preview iframe budgets, SEO metadata checks — see `web/tests/e2e/release-gates.spec.ts`.

### `sites/` (HTML templates)

- Valid HTML structure; zero console errors when opened locally
- Run the QA checklist in `.cursor/skills/html-website-builder/SKILL.md`
- Delegate `accessibility-auditor` + `performance-optimizer` + `code-reviewer` before sign-off

### `Frontend_Nextjs/` (migrated apps)

- `pnpm build` / `npm run build` with zero TypeScript errors
- Follow `.cursor/skills/nextjs-site-migrator/SKILL.md` Phase 9+ gates
- Run `nextjs-code-reviewer` before delivery

### `AI-BOS/` (isolated planning system)

- Valid YAML front matter on all new Knowledge Objects per `AI-BOS/.cursor/skills/ai-bos-architect/references/front-matter-schema.md`
- Registry integrity — objects registered in correct `knowledge-registry/*-index.json`; IDs unique across indexes
- Vendor independence — no IDE/provider lock-in in knowledge content
- Phase gate — do not advance planning phases without explicit user approval (see `AI-BOS/.cursor/skills/ai-bos-architect/checklists/phase-approval-checklist.md`)
- Structural changes route through `@system-builder`; content authoring via `@ai-bos-architect`
- Update `AI-BOS/tasks.md` with evidence before sign-off

## Never declare done when

- Module-not-found, TypeScript, or ESLint errors remain
- cSpell or other linter diagnostics remain on touched files
- `npm run build` or release gates fail
- Homepage sections were removed to "fix" performance without explicit user approval
- Merge conflict markers (`<<<<<<<`) remain in any file

## Before commit or push (when requested)

1. Re-run **`npm run ci:check --prefix web`** from repository root if any `web/` file changed (CI parity — see rule `71-git-discipline.mdc` and `/pre-push-check`).
2. Confirm `git status` has no accidental `.next/`, `.cursor/tmp-*`, or secret files staged.

Mid-phase work may use narrow lint/typecheck only; **push never skips full `ci:check`**.

**Never push** when a background or prior `ci:check` run exited non-zero or was interrupted — re-run `./web/scripts/verify-ci-parity.ps1` until exit 0.
